\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Do you remember the sort of jobs your mother would do in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Well, when - me father - m
e father fell on bad times she used to take in washing. And it was our duty - my eldest sister and myself to collect the washing and deliver the washing. And - Saturday nights we used to finish at twelve o'clock our last port of call was a doctors in Elep
hant Road on the right hand side and after that we used to go down the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392287\charrsid11030117 Caledonian}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 
 Road and shop. The stores used to be open until one o'clock and two o'clock in the morning on Caledonian Road. On a Saturday - yes. The public houses used to be open 'til twelve.
