 tap down here and when the - you wasn't allowed in the public house fourteen years of age - we could go down there and the brewers drays used to drive through and it - you used to get a half a pint of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7627976\charrsid11030117 stout}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117  in a sealed can - that used to cost threepence }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7627976\charrsid11030117 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117  can - they'd seal it up - fetch it back. Mother used to out the ginger in it, red hot poker, stir it up - an egg cup full before you went to bed. That's a fact. That was our tonic in the winter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 What time did you go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Round about - oh, not much later than - nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 At what age do you remember putting yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Well that's rather difficult. Yes, that's rather difficult. Mot
her always used - when we were quite young mother always used to come up and see we were all tucked in and all that - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Did you share the bedroom or the bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 With me brother. With me brother - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 The bed or the bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 The bedroom - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Where did the rest of the family sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 
Well they had - we had like two bedrooms you see. 'Cos when we was quite young we all slept in the one room you see, when we was quite - oh, just a see - about nine, about eig
ht or nine see, yes we slept in one room. Then after that - Liz had her own bedroom then when Rosie came along then - then the three of us shared a bed - a bed - me brother - me two brothers and myself shared one room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 And your parents had a separate room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 In the kitchen. We never - we wasn't blessed with a bathroom. It was just a - old tin bath. In front of the fire.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 How often did you have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Every Friday nights.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Did you have clean clothes put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Oh yes. Mother very particular about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 In the - in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Was there any time when they ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Only on Christmas time - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Where did your mother cook - did she have a gas stove or a range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 
No, she had - when we first remember it - there was no such thing as an oven, and we had a roasting hook and that used to dangle from here and that used to be our job to baste the ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 In front of the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 
In front of the fire - big fire. And baste the - the only time we was allowed up late at night was Christmas time and that was basting the poultry. Well, we used to get into trouble for getting a spoonful and dipping bread in. Yes, ye
s. That was roast beef - that was roast - what you call roast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Where was the fire - in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 
In the back kitchen - yes. And I believe - I don't know whether you can see it - or whether they filled it in there. No, here you are, there's the two marks here where they've had one here. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 What time did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Oh - well, before we went to school we'd have breakfast - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Would that be seven or eight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Be about or something like that - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 What member of the family were present - would you all be there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Oh they'd all be there - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 What you usually eat and drink then - you had an egg sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Yes, sometimes an egg - sometimes mother'd make - like oats. 'Cos you - not like they are now -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16392287\charrsid11030117  Quaker}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117  oats and all things prepared - they used to be - they had to be done yourself - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 What did you have to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Milk - mostly milk, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Did you have anything different on certain days for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Oh, mother used to vary it, oh yes, and - yes, and she was a great believer in rice you know - and she could make rice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 So you had quite a lot of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Oh yes, quite a lot of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 What about your mid-day meals?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Well }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7627976\charrsid11030117 now,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117  there used to be a chap come along with a - a coster barrow and on it there used to be a big barrel - like a beer barrel - open at the top and in it was all fresh herrings. Mother used to say - go out and }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7627976\charrsid11030117 get}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117  twopennorth of herrings. Well, you talk about hygiene today - he just dived his h
ands in like that and you'd hold your bowl up and you'd get splashed with everything - he'd sling 'em in the bowl - wouldn't weigh 'em - two pennorth. Well, that was one meal I could never stand - I didn't mind the fresh herrings 'cos mother used to souse
 'em but I couldn't stand the boiled - boiled potatoes with them and she used to say if you don't eat your potatoes you get no rice. So I had to eat the potatoes - yes. But - that was - must have been nutriment in that. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 What else would you have at lunch time - mid-day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 
Oh she - she was a good feeder but I tell you - now this is - this is the gospel truth and I don't mind admitting it - she used to send us to the butchers to buy two pe'nnorth of bones. Now she'd stew them on the hob - she'd
 stew them and mix different things with 'em and when she couldn't get no more out the bones I used to take them to the rag shop and get me tuppence back. It's a fact. That is the God's truth. Take the bones - big bones mind you - take them to the rag sho
p get me tuppence back. And if we fetched tuppence back into mum we was delighted. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 What did you have to eat in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Oh we, she - all had a good meal you know. Well, toast or bread and dripping or anything - oh plenty of bread and dr
ipping - she wouldn't waste nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 What would you drink then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Oh, we'd have tea then, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Did your mother bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Occasionally but not a lot - not a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Did she ever make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Oh yes, oh yes, big jars of it - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Do you remember what sort of jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Mostly plum - mostly plum, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Did she bottle fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Did she ever make pickle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Did she ever make wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 No. No, she never made wine but she - she made medicines and she also made her own ointment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 How did she do that - do you remember any particular medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Yes. Christmas time she used to always have a goose and that was roasted in front of the fire, and 
that goose fat was the ointment for all the year round, and it'd cure everything - colds and everything. It's the truth. And the medicine - I went to - a chemist - used to be Novis's, bottom of Ponder Street that is now - and I can tell you the ingredient
s now what - what it was. It was a packet of best Epsom Salts - half a box of magnesia - six drops of essence of peppermint and the juice of two lemons in a pint of water, an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7627976\charrsid11030117 egg cupful}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117  of that morning and night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Did she boil it up?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 No, just col
d - just cold, yes. And shook it up. When I went down that chemist - now all them years ago - he said to me where did you get this from? I said I don't know - my mother give it to me. He said well, tell your mother I charged you half-a-crown for it for he
r - to make it up. And that's all that was. And that was the end - and I've never thought of going to the chemist and asking them now for it but - that used to get rid of colds and everything else I think. Boils, yes, it did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Did your father or mother grow their own vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 You didn't have any space?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 No. We - not - did have a bit of a garden but they never - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Did they brew beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 No. Dad was a strong }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7627976\charrsid11030117 teetotaler}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117  - well, near enough strong }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7627976\charrsid11030117 teetotaler}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117  wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Did they buy any tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Did they keep any livestock - hens, or pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Oh, only once - me father tried - chickens, but that didn't last long. It was a - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7627976\charrsid11030117 oh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117  - he bought - I must tell you this, this is the truth. They all - he bought half a dozen pullets and they all turned out to be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7627976\charrsid11030117 cockerels}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 
 barring one hen. Well they fought so much that my mother locked them in the front coal cellar. Well, she goes to get some coal - forgot about the chickens 
- she opened the door. One of them went to run out and she shut the door. Well, that killed it so that's how she killed the cockerel off, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Did your father look after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Oh yes, he looked after them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Do you remember how many times a week you ate meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16531778 HE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Well, I should say - say - Sunday and then cold meat on Monday. But the rest of the week it used to be more or less stews.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11407999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11226032\charrsid11030117 Just the meat from the bones?
